//why? Jade has interpolation yes thats true, but when querying the db for data we want to insert data into placeholders that will be pushed back to the db, this means post interpolation is needed, we are just proccessing strings with regex.
//Example usage
//a string of jade or anything, @{objkey} will be found and replaced with its value, its an object so can use more than once replacement.

//var str = "some post interpolation @{testData} for jade markup using js api"
